glosses: to carry, carry away, transport from one place to another
to bear, carry, possess, have, keep
to bear, endure, put up with

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish طاشیمق (taşımak, “to bear, support, sustain, carry, transport”), from Proto-Turkic [Term?].
Cognates
Cognate with Karakhanid [script needed] (taşūmāk, “to carry, transfer”), Azerbaijani daşımaq (“to carry, transfer, bear”), Bashkir ташыу (taşıw, “to carry”), Chagatai [script needed] (taşımaq, “to transport”), Khakas тазирға (tazirğa, “to carry”), Kazakh тасу (tasu, “to carry”), Kipchak [Arabic needed] (taşı-, “to transfer, convey”), Kyrgyz ташуу (taşuu, “to carry”), Southern Altai тажыыр (tažïïr, “to carry”), Tatar ташу (taşu, “to carry”), Turkmen daşamak (“to carry”), Tuvan дажыыр (dajıır, “to carry”), Uyghur توشۇماق (toshumaq, “to transport, carry”), Uzbek tashimoq (“to carry, transfer”).
